text: Faustin-Archange Touadéra (French: [fostɛ̃ aʁkɑ̃ʒ twadeʁa]; born 21 April 1957) is a Central African politician and academic who has been President of the Central African Republic since March 2016. He was previously Prime Minister of the country from January 2008 to January 2013. ==References== Category:1957 births Category:Presidents of the Central Africa Republic Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of the Central African Republic Category:Current national leaders
